item.title: [3ds] sparkplug
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

[quote=“jjones10, post:8, topic:290376”][quote author=CoonHunter link=topic=383884.msg2882350#msg2882350 date=1248408571]

A SparkPlug lolz thats random.

I like the Colour of that wood peice

Kinda had to lol at this, spark plugs have no wood on them at all. The part your referring to as “wood” is actually a small aluminum piece. Cant assume we all know this though. I just grew up around my papa who works on cars for a living. So i know a decent amount about the stuff.
[/quote]
Exactly. The plug i changed was all burnt on the bottom because this dumb ass’s turbo caught on fire. so i decided to make it brownish because thats exactly what it looked like.

[offtopic but important]Remember to use anti-freeze children. Cold water does not cut it when you are street racing…[/offtopic but important][/quote]
OMFG, he honestly used cold water? I wont run anything but super grade fuel and anti-freeze in my car. Alas, the one i am buying is a Dodge Neon SRT-4. They will do 130 easy stock. Well, that or I will restore this charger my neighbor is thinking about giving me.
